Walking Robot

A simple command-line based script in PHP which accepts a command line argument as an input string of the current position, direction and walking code and print out the result of the last position of the robot.

Input Format:

X Y D S

X = Current X position
Y = Current Y position
D = Current direction robot is facing (North, East, South or West)
S = Walk string

Output Format:

X Y D

X = Current X position
Y = Current Y position
D = Current direction robot is facing (North, East, South or West) 


Example:

$ php walkingRobot.php 5 2 NORTH LW2RR
$ X - axis : 3
  Y - axis : 2
  EAST direction

Note:
1. R : Turn 90 degree on right (clockwise).
2. L : Turn 90 degree on left (counterclockwise).
3. WN : Walk forward N units in the direction robot is facing. For example, W2 means robot walks 2 unit point forward


